@startuml decorator-structure-abstract
' Decorator, Structural. Abstract structure: canonical GoF roles only.
' The Decorator both extends Component and holds a Component, so behavior stacks.
!include ../../pattern-preamble.iuml

interface Component STRUCTURAL_ROLE(Component) {
  +operation()
}
class ConcreteComponent STRUCTURAL_ROLE(ConcreteComponent) {
  +operation()
}
abstract class Decorator STRUCTURAL_ROLE(Decorator) {
  #wrapped : Component
  +operation()
}
class ConcreteDecorator STRUCTURAL_ROLE(ConcreteDecorator) {
  +operation()
  +addedBehavior()
}

Component <|.. ConcreteComponent
Component <|.. Decorator
Decorator <|-- ConcreteDecorator
Decorator o-- Component : wrapped

note as N
  Intent: add responsibilities to one object at runtime without subclassing the class.
  Consequence: many small wrapper objects; debugging a deep stack of decorators is harder.
end note
@enduml
